article.description: Gordon Hayward scored 25 points to lead Butler (No. 18 ESPN/USA Today) to its 10th win in a row, a 73-66 victory over Wisconsin-Milwaukee on Sunday.
article.headline: Hayward scores 25 as Butler wins 10th straight
article.linkText: Hayward lifts No. 18 Butler to 10th straight win

inlines.body:
Fast Facts

• The Bulldogs won their 10th straight game, thanks to Gordon Hayward's 12th career 20-plus point game.

• The Bulldogs have won 17 of their last 18 games against unranked opponents and eight of their last nine conference road games.

• For the Panthers, Anthony Hill set a career high with 21 points, but the team lost for the seventh time in their last eight against Butler.

-- ESPN Stats & Information

article.story: MILWAUKEE -- Gordon Hayward scored 25 points to lead Butler (No. 18 ESPN/USA Today) to its 10th win in a row, a 73-66 victory over Wisconsin-Milwaukee on Sunday. Ronald Nored and Shelvin Mack added 13 points apiece for the Bulldogs (18-4, 11-0), who are aiming for their fourth consecutive Horizon League championship. Anthony Hill scored a career-high 21 points for Wisconsin-Milwaukee (13-10, 5-6). Willie Veasley's basket ended an 8-0 Butler run, putting the Bulldogs up 58-55 midway through the second half. The Panthers came within 65-64 on a 3-pointer by James Eayrs, but Butler pulled away at the end. Hill scored 12 points in the first half as the Panthers led 35-34 at the break.
